[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating reflection requirements**\n\nI’m thinking about how ReflectUtils.findDeclaredMethod uses getDeclaredMethod, and whether it needs metadata. In a native image, runtime reflection might require test class registration if there aren’t any constants. I wonder if the native image can intercept constant class or method names. When it comes to cglib, existing tests probably rely on agent-generated metadata, while user filters include only cglib. If metadata generation excludes test classes, native image reflection on test beans might fail. Yet, BeanCopier uses Introspector instead of metadata?\n\n**Analyzing metadata generation**\n\nI’m considering how the user’s code filter excludes everything and only includes cglib in the agent condition. This means generated metadata will likely only cover net.sf.cglib, leaving out test helpers. I wonder if Graal can incorporate reflection metadata for JUnit discovery, registering test and nested classes. Native build tools might include the reflection config for tests. However, generated CGLIB classes invoke getters and setters directly, avoiding reflection at runtime. Perhaps I should only instantiate `Generator` without creating a dynamic class. This can trigger the static initialization needed while ensuring coverage.\n\n**Improving test coverage**\n\nI see that the user wants to improve test coverage for an active dynamic-access class, possibly to reach uncovered call sites while ensuring high coverage through integration testing. It could involve both generator initialization and the creation process. If the creation step fails in a native context, there's a potential risk. Existing cglib tests show that dynamic classes like BeanCopier work well. I should verify that BulkBean operates similarly and assess potential issues involving the naming conventions of nested classes. The generated class may end up in the cglib.cglib_nodep package, which is worth noting.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_07b9c9d91f1d08da0169ef6b213c148197b236dc5dc7b2be58\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp72st3n5u7vmdsCzB0Thf1KThqQRdjpEhH4z_r2fazl3UDfua8A8hYSOcD8CUanIwWJ1A7WW03ybZOSnywteq1Ce9LKzkFJHJXIO6_BGEcEWr1X60jS7lFejWDjuxCK2vhoOuHP0DOkURSJ3BQyWgGEpcJx-hszKZHTkeBZzd2fKd1a3tteH837R_AJiCJhzF_aCzNhzvZIk-r7epJ75hhLHsIFGEe8P1IHcNpaI07rWUwED5ehZO9qqkfBenNrWe51tW3SydJHoVvz0zuj2Lt92JP_8zmnmKJWD7pB-Lsus3rYOQTFtN-COb-piqLjZDd3xLb5E3bWVNaHMXZhrW-UY-8NK3yS3o_pl4F28z7JNk42kutsexgUn8MPc-PQpImmGAIPsbKMhh8R97ZhAHZ3tiENsHnTc3o2zTiRVBiMtGYYWEHfaLwZIyPHfHm31R3X85Nu_PLAaEGxVTdST8jGSEaybUBjZ9mCjpI7Auin3a7HuqpYOyy041EcuHjxsT1rFO9OPLhB6sR4Pd-Tcb3ePwdtV88BLH-dHLn5NrVOxXXeDt5u0Zvo8T_X5jv-FyeO_SKcAwrkRLJa_gvoCxE-Wli3cBFNd2zzqnOOBtzlM-uPcRlrCD05fVN49aK0RxtMyJBLkQ2nJkrES8CetIq45kvXAr7mIQ3If6q0IyVl50Ig8fIhhwmwCewIDNjMEaRhWfhJJjhhVVlzBCarRrTnhaoEfiH5ZXcBK1bielyevzfDXw9Q4UdysWUXzz8om8JlF15SR9ooCIv6SAX2nSY7Tr_aNf_nGEy4YQqcv4GBUKp0Yu6X_o3kUH8BB32R-IgKVHSk6nXmQalRrLuX9IjiReAuOxPAsTH0Tykq6xXoY9H31ZQZtJMrQS2Vh28QfBz1nJC8JPB88Kz-SB92t8CkTH24Pr7ZwY_7_cGXW09xtyoz5DZbF0CjI14UjIqSXGQu14apn02o5Ei-vMXs7EPpMfqn2-y9IuqdYFbTp1y1rmibN-e2Cltq7nLOa8zR51TW5G-F-qnee_jY6ezHiyFfh94jqO9FTcnY6EKfZfjO53pFm-1aUAFORXBwvF9bvLWcSM3KHvncFehI6ZJsDEikov5awrZ5OZaVh2iUKPLGK5Io2FjEjccDD4NfRbVgCta2g9Y6PrW8rmhafls0dWc1J4qTyVkXJj5-95jO_x7uOAQ3UzXWi9XvfEKAScHPeuEOkviYothRXCwJOUbJkb3hbBb3nlE9gCy8xxwMxP-WargIn3TW0TJZu1nvOvk4pPHsLASqo6w8HJGc35ggE3SuVbXhYTz2MUoZK2J2n5owyYLGJ3e_BdFNgpfNzUDUmrrWNHp8ILM3uCbbLIYG96yoFif4BtmKG2T08jBx0KTiZBD6PXvXW89IZdcddQRSKmpSMRg7Opa94g2fzef50OHmtfDn8O__V5vVtFgzdg5wvNNqkwaJN2o3ybusZhdNGLRKkTp4WdkJ83IgHmK_j_8rG8LbrTai8l1U9jTWGZ3kWNFKQSrPorloalCtM60LGa9sMZTHAgnKyHGwPYKFxrjLC2Fa1SU8Fmts2_UW5vBQFIO850g2z-ZmMdkfCcUJpOsxmoJIDgt5JVRXLRWstpbK_y4xGgTtmLCX5nPyzOkh8Tn5ua4Bl0_69rNCreSf3kT5-w6HuKz6E_SEZ4jJLMU57U2iqPXrp82oKDfOoQ9tMG_meNn6Vk9iZ4scIt1hOVshMtICOFn8ULPODR9W0rHPwKQPyu3vwZNy7UM6SIHgZ8hu2LI3jooHx6F-jajwsTgkIdAV6gY63k