eaking the rule against direct reflection since it's private package access. Another thought is to explore using `ClassLoader.loadClass`, which is also considered direct reflection. I’m thinking about whether the public API, specifically the static initializer in BulkBean.Generator, would allow for calling `BulkBean.class$` when it's first used.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering public API requirements**\\n\\nI’m wondering if the phrase \\\"public API requires it naturally\\\" pertains to the `BulkBean.create` API needing a class to be passed. It's interesting that using class literals for RecordBean seems acceptable. To initiate the static initializer after instrumentation starts, I need to avoid any references to BulkBean before the test body. However, it seems that import and bytecode method references don’t trigger initialization, which adds to the complexity of the situation.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering initialization methods**\\n\\nI'm noticing that direct static methods initialize the outer components first. I think it might be helpful to modify the initial test to use a static factory instead of generator initialization. Alternatively, I could add a new @Order(1) for the direct static method. After that, I should consider shifting things around based on this new approach. There seems to be some flexibility in how this could all come together!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_QtSNhc8F3z3bwtBlmckT9HRu|fc_07b9c9d91f1d08da0169ef6bc908e881978a31e8ec21512738", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/BulkBeanTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    void initializesPublicGenerator() {\n        BulkBean.Generator generator = new BulkBean.Generator();\n\n        assertThat(generator).isNotNull();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @Order(2)\n    void createsBulkAccessorThroughConfiguredGenerator() {", "newText": "    void createsBulkAccessorThroughStaticFactory() {\n        BulkBean bulkBean = BulkBean.create(RecordBean.class, GETTERS, SETTERS, TYPES);\n        RecordBean bean = new RecordBean();\n        Object[] values = {\"Ada\", 37, true, 99L, 'G'};\n\n        bulkBean.setPropertyValues(bean, values);\n        Object[] actualValues = bulkBean.getPropertyValues(bean);\n\n        assertThat(actualValues).containsExactly(values);\n        assertThat(bean.getName()).isEqualTo(\"Ada\");\n        assertThat(bean.getAge()).isEqualTo(37);\n        assertThat(bean.isActive()).isTrue();\n        assertThat(bean.getScore()).isEqualTo(99L);\n        assertThat(bean.getCode()).isEqualTo('G');\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @Order(2)\n    void initializesPublicGenerator() {\n        BulkBean.Generator generator = new BulkBean.Generator();\n\n        assertThat(generator).isNotNull();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @Order(3)\n    void createsBulkAccessorThroughConfiguredGenerator() {"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    @Order(3)\n    void readsAndWritesBeanPropertiesInBulk() {\n        BulkBean bulkBean = BulkBean.create(RecordBean.class, GETTERS, SETTERS, TYPES);\n        RecordBean bean = new RecordBean();\n        Object[] values = {\"Ada\", 37, true, 99L, 'G'};\n\n        bulkBean.setPropertyValues(bean, values);\n        Object[] actualValues = bulkBean.getPropertyValues(bean);\n\n        assertThat(actualValues).containsExactly(values);\n        assertThat(bean.getName()).isEqualTo(\"Ada\");\n        assertThat(bean.getAge()).isEqualTo(37);\n        assertThat(bean.isActive()).isTrue();\n        assertThat(bean.getScore()).isEqualTo(99L);\n        assertThat(bean.getCode()).isEqualTo('G');\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @Order(4)\n    void reportsAccessorValidationFailuresWithPropertyIndex() {", "newText": "    @Test\n    @Order(4)\n    void reportsAccessorValidationFailuresWithPropertyIndex() {"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2629, "output": 2760, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "tota